Good evening,

33:52.405 --> 33:53.622
Fortitude!

34:21.518 --> 34:24.271
Hey, kiddo.

34:25.772 --> 34:27.649
I got you something.

34:55.594 --> 34:58.814
I'm on the door until 2:00
and then Truls takes over.

34:58.972 --> 34:59.939
Why don't you go home?

35:00.098 --> 35:02.851
Get some proper sleep.

35:03.018 --> 35:05.066
I've been told
it's family only.

35:05.228 --> 35:07.196
Just you and your wife?

35:07.355 --> 35:09.528
That's right. What shall I
say to the Spanish girl

35:09.691 --> 35:10.943
if she comes back?

35:11.109 --> 35:12.861
She said she was
a friend of the family.

35:14.112 --> 35:16.365
She was here?
Yes, last night.

35:16.531 --> 35:17.874
Liam was asleep.

35:18.033 --> 35:20.502
She just talked to him.

35:22.078 --> 35:23.580
To be honest,
we did feel sorry for you,

35:23.747 --> 35:26.421
me and Pettie.

35:26.583 --> 35:28.005
Alone in-in that cell.

35:28.168 --> 35:30.591
All night.

35:30.754 --> 35:33.223
Well, you should have come
and paid me a visit then.

35:35.091 --> 35:38.015
Yeah, that would have been
very unprofessional.

35:38.178 --> 35:39.600
Yeah.

35:41.389 --> 35:43.483
To wrongful arrests.

36:03.620 --> 36:04.963
Hello.

36:10.543 --> 36:13.387
Uh, Governor Odegard

36:13.546 --> 36:15.389
wanted to say a few words,

36:15.548 --> 36:18.017
but she can't make it.

36:18.176 --> 36:20.019
So, uh, it's going to be me.

36:20.178 --> 36:21.430
Yeah!

36:21.596 --> 36:23.223
At least it'll be short.

36:25.558 --> 36:28.107
We're here to say good-bye
to mine seven

36:28.269 --> 36:30.988
and some of the men
who worked there.

36:31.147 --> 36:34.196
When people think of this place,

36:34.359 --> 36:37.283
they think of the... the ice,

36:37.445 --> 36:40.198
the bears, the mountains.

36:41.491 --> 36:43.539
That's what we want 'em to see.

36:43.702 --> 36:46.922
But you've spent
your lives

36:47.080 --> 36:49.549
working under the surface.

36:49.708 --> 36:52.052
In the darkness.

36:52.210 --> 36:54.713
You did it the hard way.

36:54.879 --> 36:56.802
And I wish, uh,

36:56.965 --> 36:58.842
you were leaving
in better times.

37:03.221 --> 37:04.393
What's happened

37:04.556 --> 37:06.103
during the past few days...

37:06.266 --> 37:08.143
is...

37:09.436 --> 37:10.779
...inexplicable.

37:10.937 --> 37:13.031
I...

37:13.189 --> 37:15.032
I-I never thought
something like that

37:15.191 --> 37:17.159
could happen here.

37:21.990 --> 37:26.211
We're a...

37:26.369 --> 37:29.373
we're a few hundred people

37:29.539 --> 37:31.382
gripping onto a rock

37:31.541 --> 37:33.714
in the middle
of the Arctic Ocean.

37:33.877 --> 37:36.130
We're alone.

37:38.673 --> 37:40.471
We need each other.

37:42.260 --> 37:45.514
And when we lose
someone from the town,

37:45.680 --> 37:48.103
we feel it.

37:48.266 --> 37:51.440
That also makes us strong.

37:51.603 --> 37:53.856
Together.

37:54.022 --> 37:57.777
It'll take time for
us to get over this,

37:57.942 --> 38:00.786
but we will.

38:00.945 --> 38:03.164
Summer's coming.

38:03.323 --> 38:05.701
There will be better days.

38:05.867 --> 38:07.665
Yeah. Yeah.

38:07.827 --> 38:10.080
So...

38:10.246 --> 38:12.465
for those of you
who are leaving us,

38:12.624 --> 38:14.422
<i>farvel ha det bra.</i>

38:14.584 --> 38:15.631
